                        <td>Test port connectivity inside container</td>
                        <td>✅ Complete</td>
                        <td>curl to localhost:3000 returns "Connection refused" - nothing listening on port</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>5</td>
                        <td>Analyze docker-entrypoint.sh permissions logic</td>
                        <td>✅ Complete</td>
                        <td>Found chmod 755 on log directory - insufficient for comserv user write access</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>6</td>
                        <td>Review create-supervisor-config.sh user configuration</td>
                        <td>✅ Complete</td>
                        <td>Supervisor configured to run as <code>user=comserv</code>, but directory lacks write permissions</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>7</td>
                        <td>Verify Dockerfile user setup</td>
                        <td>✅ Complete</td>
                        <td>Dockerfile correctly creates comserv user and chowns /opt/comserv, but entrypoint undoes this</td>
                    </tr>
