        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container success" id="findings">
    <div class="container-header">Key Findings Summary</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Finding 1: Permission Mismatch</h3>
            <p><strong>Log Directory Permissions Issue</strong>: Directory created as <code>755</code> (root-owned) prevents comserv user from writing to catalyst.log</p>
            
            <h3>Finding 2: Supervisor Process Failure</h3>
            <p><strong>No Application Process Running</strong>: Supervisor fails to spawn comserv-server due to permission error. Only supervisord daemon is running.</p>
            
            <h3>Finding 3: Port Unbound</h3>
            <p><strong>Port 3000 Not Listening</strong>: Since Starman/Perl application never starts, port 3000 has no service listening. Connection attempts time out.</p>
            
            <h3>Finding 4: Health Check Fails</h3>
            <p><strong>Unhealthy Container Status</strong>: Health check in docker-compose tries to curl http://localhost:3000/health but gets connection refused, marking container unhealthy</p>
            
            <h3>Finding 5: Application Runs Fine Locally</h3>
            <p><strong>No Code Issues</strong>: Application works perfectly when run from command line (perl script/comserv_server.pl) - confirms this is purely a containerization/permission issue, not application logic</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container info" id="solution">
    <div class="container-header">Solution & Fix</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Fix: Update docker-entrypoint.sh Permissions</h3>
            
            <p><strong>Change this (lines 91-93):</strong></p>
            <pre><code>mkdir -p ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor
chmod 755 ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>To this:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>mkdir -p ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor
chmod 755 ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor
chown -R comserv:comserv ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Alternative Solution (More Permissive)</h3>
            <p>If the above doesn't work, use:</p>
            <pre><code>mkdir -p ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor
chmod 777 ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log /var/log/supervisor
chown -R comserv:comserv ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Why This Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><code>mkdir -p</code> - Ensures directories exist</li>
                <li><code>chmod 755</code> - Ensures proper read/execute for others</li>
                <li><code>chown -R comserv:comserv</code> - <strong>KEY FIX</strong> - Makes comserv the owner, ensuring write permissions</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>Implementation Steps</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Edit <code>Comserv/docker-entrypoint.sh</code></li>
                <li>Locate lines 91-93 (after the comment about supervisor socket)</li>
                <li>Add the <code>chown</code> command</li>
                <li>Rebuild Docker image: <code>docker-compose build</code></li>
                <li>Restart container: <code>docker-compose down && docker-compose up</code></li>
                <li>Verify port 3000 responds</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container warning" id="verification">
    <div class="container-header">Verification & Testing</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Before Fix (Current State)</h3>
            <pre><code>$ curl http://localhost:3000/
curl: (7) Failed to connect to localhost port 3000 after 2 ms: Couldn't connect to server

$ docker ps
CONTAINER ID   STATUS           NAMES
e76bd136da89   Up 16h (unhealthy)   comserv-web-dev

$ docker logs comserv-web-dev | grep EACCES
INFO spawnerr: unknown error making dispatchers for 'comserv-server': EACCES</code></pre>
            
            <h3>After Fix (Expected)</h3>
            <pre><code>$ curl http://localhost:3000/
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
[HTML content of Comserv application page]

$ docker ps
CONTAINER ID   STATUS           NAMES
e76bd136da89   Up 16h (healthy)    comserv-web-dev

$ docker logs comserv-web-dev | grep FATAL
[No FATAL errors]</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Testing Checklist</h3>
            <table class="diagnostic-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Test</th>
                        <th>Command/Action</th>
                        <th>Expected Result</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Port Connection</td>
                        <td><code>curl http://localhost:3000/</code></td>
                        <td>HTTP 200 with HTML content</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Container Health</td>
                        <td><code>docker ps --format "table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}"</code></td>
                        <td>Status shows "(healthy)" not "(unhealthy)"</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Process Running</td>
                        <td><code>docker exec [container] ps aux | grep starman</code></td>
                        <td>Starman process with PID and workers visible</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Log Files</td>
                        <td><code>docker exec [container] ls -la /opt/comserv/root/log/</code></td>
                        <td>catalyst.log and catalyst_error.log exist and are writable</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>No EACCES Errors</td>
                        <td><code>docker logs [container] | grep EACCES</code></td>
                        <td>No output (no errors found)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Health Endpoint</td>
                        <td><code>curl http://localhost:3000/health</code></td>
                        <td>JSON response: {"status":"ok"} or similar</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container" id="additional_notes">
    <div class="container-header">Additional Notes & Recommendations</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Resource Conservation</h3>
            <p>This investigation was optimized for low-resource environments by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ Documenting findings in real-time (.tt file created during investigation)</li>
                <li>✅ Running parallel diagnostic commands to reduce total time</li>
                <li>✅ Focusing on the most likely cause (permission errors) first</li>
                <li>✅ Using existing container logs rather than creating new test containers</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Future Prevention</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Consider using <code>chown</code> in Dockerfile instead of relying on entrypoint</li>
                <li>Add explicit permission checks in docker-entrypoint.sh diagnostic output</li>
                <li>Update health check to include permission verification as part of startup</li>
                <li>Document permission requirements in docker-compose comments</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Related Docker/Kubernetes Files</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><code>docker-entrypoint.sh</code> - Fix location</li>
                <li><code>create-supervisor-config.sh</code> - Supervisor process configuration</li>
                <li><code>supervisord.conf</code> - Supervisor base configuration</li>
                <li><code>Dockerfile</code> - Image build configuration</li>
                <li><code>docker-compose.yml</code> - Container orchestration (root level)</li>
                <li><code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code> - Development-specific overrides</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

